text.tspan: mergePairs says: denoised F1 is paired with R1, here is how abundance is found
of FW and RV IDs, to find actually
paired reads, NB: demands FW and
NB2: it is well possible that the same FW denoised
sequence has paired with several R denoised sequences!
F_drp is the output of derepFastq, a derep_class object
$uniques: what unique reads were there and how abundant (usually most were there only once)
$quals: the average quality of each unique read at each cycle
$maps: an integer of the length of the filtered reads telling to which unique read it is mapped
>> length($maps) tells you how many filtered reads there were
>> length($unique) tells you how many unique reads there were
F_dd is a dada_class object the output of the dada command:
$denoised: the number of denoised reads/sequencing and how abundant they are, so length($denoised) = so many final reads are considered real,
NB: sum($denoised) <= sum(F_drp$uniques), meaning that some unique reads must be considered errors without being assigned to a denoised sequence.
Maybe that is the singleton removal.
$map: an integer of the length of the unique reads telling to which denoised sequence it is mapped
